  "type": "mcq",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">An elementary school teacher is ordering <span class=\"italic\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic \">x</span></span> workbooks and <span class=\"italic\">y</span> sets of flash cards for a math class. The teacher must order at least 20 items, but the total cost of the order must not be over $80. If the workbooks cost $3 each and the flash cards cost $4 per set, which of the following systems of inequalities models this situation?</p>\n",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \"><span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x plus y, is greater than or equal to 20, and, 3 x plus 4 y, is less than or equal to 80\n\"></span></span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \"><span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x plus y, is greater than or equal to 20, and, 3 x plus 4 y, is greater than or equal to 80\n\"></span></span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \"><span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 x plus 4 y, is less than or equal to 20, and, x plus y, is greater than or equal to 80\n\"></span></span></p>\n"
